http://www.thehindu.com/sport/tennis/Vijay-stuns-top-seed-Nagal/article14643590.ece

 Fifth seed N. Vijay Sundar Prashanth staged a brilliant fightback to defeat top seed Sumit Nagal 6-7(3), 6-4, 6-4 for a place in the semifinals of the LMW-ITF Futures tournament at the Perks Tennis Centre here on Thursday.Second seed Prajnesh Gunneswaran and No. 3 Vishnu Vardhan were put to test too by lower-ranked opponents on a hot sunny afternoon but managed to come out trumps.Nagal started rather shakily against Vijay. The 19-year-old from Chandigarh looked out of sorts early in the first set and Vijay cashed in to take a 4-1 lead.But Nagal stemmed the rot and bounced back in style. He matched Vijay stroke for stroke; he served big and hit winners time and again to take the set into the tie-break, which he won with ease. Equally, Vijay could well have sealed the set if not for a host of unforced errors.With the first set in his bag, Nagal applied pressure on Vijay. But the latter upped the pace; he rallied strongly from the baseline and even approached the net on occasion, to wrap up the next two sets and the match.Earlier, Prajnesh survived some anxious moments before getting past a fighting Sidharth Rawat, the eighth seed, 6-7(5), 6-3, 7-5, while Vishnu scored a 7-6(9), 7-5 win over seventh seed Sasi Kumar Mukund.Balaji & Vishnu in finalSriram Balaji and Vishnu defeated Mohit Mayur and Kaza Vinayak Sharma 6-4, 6-4 to enter the doubles final.The duo will now take on Anvit Bendre and Vijay who defeated Fahad Mohammed and Abhinav Sanjeev Shanmugam 6-4, 7-6(3).The results: Quarterfinals: Sanam Singh bt N. Sriram Balaji 1-6, 6-1, 6-3; Prajnesh Gunneswaran bt Sidharth Rawat 6-7(5), 6-3, 7-5, Vishnu Vardhan bt Sasi Kumar Mukund 7-6(9), 7-5, Vijay Sundar Prashanth bt Sumit Nagal 6-7(3), 6-4, 6-4. Doubles: Semifinals: Sriram Balaji & Vishnu Vardhan bt Mohit Mayur & Kaza Vinayak Sharma 6-4, 6-4; Anvit Bendre & Vijay Sundar Prashanth bt Fahad Mohammed & Abhinav Sanjeev Shanmugam 6-4, 7-6(3).